getLoginKey

public static java.lang.String getLoginKey(java.lang.String course,
                                           java.lang.String user,
                                           java.lang.String set)
                                    throws java.rmi.RemoteException
Generates a login Key for the webwork course and the user. Returns the login key back to blackboard. Method is synchronized, so that only one user can get the login key at a time. Thus, one person login key does not messes up with the other person's key.

Returns:
the LoginKey
Throws:
java.rmi.RemoteException

getEncryptedValue

public static java.lang.String getEncryptedValue(java.lang.String dataToEncrypt)
Generates an ecrypted hash value for the string generated. If security is needed this method is used, else it wont be used.

Parameters:
dataToEncrypt - String value which needs to be encrypted.
Returns:
String value of the bytes returned by the encrypted string.
